# The repo already ships a root `.npmrc` with only:
#   @czechcanoe:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com/
# Put your token in your user-level npmrc (recommended) so it is never committed:
#   Windows: %USERPROFILE%\.npmrc
#   macOS/Linux: ~/.npmrc
#
# Add one line (replace YOUR_TOKEN; no quotes):
#   //npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=YOUR_TOKEN
#
# Or for a single shell session:
#   set NODE_AUTH_TOKEN=YOUR_TOKEN   (cmd)
#   $env:NODE_AUTH_TOKEN = "YOUR_TOKEN"   (PowerShell)
#
# Token: GitHub → Settings → Developer settings → Personal access tokens
# Classic: "read:packages" (and "repo" if needed). Fine-grained: Packages → Read + SSO authorize for CzechCanoe.
